  "commentary": "With SPX at 6759.81 sitting right in the heart of massive negative gamma clusters (6765 at -6.9B, 6770 at -4.9B), dealers are forced to buy this dip aggressively as their short gamma positions amplify the move lower. The PIN regime suggests mean reversion bias, but the concentration of negative GEX around current levels means any bounce will face immediate dealer selling pressure once we approach the 6800 positive gamma wall (+6.0B). Watch 6765 as the critical amplification level - a break below triggers more dealer buying, while reclaim of 6770-6800 corridor should see stabilizing dealer selling.\n\nBottom line: expect a bounce from current levels but capped near 6800.",
